              <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-6">ECE Certification Levels in BC (2026)</h2>
              <ul class="space-y-3 text-slate-700">
                <li><strong>ECE Assistant:</strong> Entry-level role under supervision. No formal certification required, but Criminal Record Review and first aid mandatory.</li>
                <li><strong>ECE Basic (NOC 42202):</strong> One-year college certificate or 47 credit hours. Wage range $22-28/hr plus $4/hr provincial wage enhancement.</li>
                <li><strong>ECE Infant/Toddler:</strong> ECE Basic + 500 supervised hours and additional training. Wage range $26-32/hr plus enhancement.</li>
                <li><strong>ECE Special Needs:</strong> ECE Basic + special needs specialization. Wage range $27-34/hr plus enhancement.</li>
              </ul>
